nodes.bodyText:
Are you asking me for my opinion on
update("name", "Mortal").with("status", Status.Alive);
being different than
update("name = 'Mortal' where status = ?1", Status.Alive);
Would be cool to be unified but I imagine there is a reason behind that difference?
What makes me uneasy is how can I do a update all name to "Mortal" without condition of being alive? And the counter reason is how is it clear that I am not changing all the DB by accident by forgetting the "where clause" - that could not have happened ever to one of us, right so this is purely hypothetical that an ecomerce site did update its catalog with price=0 for all products ;P

