nodes.bodyText:
@emmanuelbernard in fact the implementation is
update(filter, params).with(document, params)
So
update("name", "Mortal").with("status", Status.Alive);
Correspond to the following one implemented on Hibernate with Panache (but cannot be done easily with MongoDB)
update("name = ?1 where status = ?2", "Mortal", Status.Alive);
To update without filter you could use the empty String or null (worth testing it)
update("").with("status", Status.Alive);
We can also add an overload of update with no parameters for this case, good point :)

